caption: Best bar in Boston. Been coming here with my friends for years and will always have a special place with me. The food is awesome (definitely the best chicken wings you'll find in Boston), lively music, awesome staff. Made some of my best memories at this place.
Suggested tip is to be paid compulsory No song favours Service is delayed Soju shots are good
Loved the food!

Walked in and the bouncer was being extremely rude to people waiting. I should have known from that to turn around but my excitement for Korean food kept me in line. Placed a reservation the day before and was told they don't take reservations when I got there. On the phone we were also told that the minimum per person was $25 and then when we got there it was $30. Waitstaff was the rudest I've ever encountered and the manager was even worse. Please avoid this place unless you're taking someone whose night you want to ruin.
The vibe and music is great even for a week night!
Food excellent,  dope environment

It's a covid Friday night at 7:30pm and there's a huge line out the door. Thankfully, we have a reservation so we don't have to wait out in the cold for very long.  At the door, they incorrectly marked us with X's on our hands to indicate we couldn't order alcohol even though we were 23-24 years old. I tried to clarify multiple times that were were all 21+ before they marked our hands and their Sharpied us anyways. Later we insisted that we were all of age and all provided ID and were told that if we had fakes, that they would keep them. This experience kind of annoyed us, but we were still able to order alcohol as usual.  The place is packed with a party atmosphere. The music is pumping, it's dark, and hard to hear each other.  We ordered kimchi pancakes, ddukbokki AKA tteok-bokki, boodae jungol AKA army stew, spicy squid, stone bowl bibibop, and garlic noodles. This was plenty of food for 6 people and we cleared nearly everything. All their food is amazing and not too spicy even though I have a tough time with spicy food. Their portion size is really good for the price.  I'm knocking it down a star for the trouble with the 21+ mix up and the food is pretty slow to show up, but we had lots of good company at the table.  During covid, you can't just order drinks, even if you plan on ordering food in 10 minutes; you have to order some kind of food with your drinks. There has to be a minimum of $25 spent per person as well.
Nice atmosphere. Drinks were so so as well as the food.

This was the only bar in Boston nearby our hotel that was open till 2AM on a Friday during Covid. We stopped in, bouncer was friendly, sat us down, and our waitress came out within seconds of seating. They did a great job working with covid regulations and still provided a fun place to go. The only reason I don’t give it 5 stars is because our waitress wasn’t  super friendly, seemed like she had a stressful night. She was a little rushed as well and messed up our drink orders. They had good music, good lighting, and the food was better than any other place we ate at that night! It was fresh, hot, and took less than 10 minutes. We were amazed at how fast it was with how busy it was. The other bouncer that stays in the middle of the room was super kind too. He walked me to the bathroom because I couldn't find it. Both bouncers would open doors for us ladies and was just kind. Good food, good drinks, and average service.

Great ambience, designed cocktails but the place is not worth it. We were a group and every drink/Soju we ordered simply tasted like fruit juices. Imagine ordering the 40$ Watermelon Soju which actually comes in half cut watermelon and it simply tastes watermelon juice. There was hardly any or no liquor in their cocktails. Highly highly recommend to not order any drinks from their menu. The food was average. Ambience is great and the waitresses are trained to make your bill bigger and rip you.
Nice place. good environment. Cute servers. 😁

The menu was very extensive and had a huge variety of great Korean dishes. The food was spectacular. I used to live in Korea and struggle to find Korean restaurants in America that feel authentic. And the food and flavor here was awesome. Portion sizes were great. However, Korean restaurants are expensive in the US so I feel as if my service should be on point with it. We ordered a Soju and beer tower. I took a sip from the glass and I had to pull something out of my mouth. I literally pulled something 2-3 inches long out of my mouth on my first sip. It could have been a paper towel I’m not even sure what it was and neither did the waiter. They did give us a new tower, fine. We were polite and moved on. We ordered bulgogi but received a super spicy meat dish instead which we didn’t order. They took it back, the waiter came over and apologized for mis-hearing me and gave us what we ordered instead. Fine. By the time the dish we ordered came, we were already practically done with the rest of our meal. So two negative things happened during my experience at this expensive restaurant and nothing was comped out. I just feel like something a little more should have been done to make our experience a little better after these two mistakes. Although the food was good, I won’t be going back. Not worth the money to deal with mistakes like that with nothing in return. I felt like a “sorry” isn’t sufficient when my bill is $160.

I went there last friday with my gf, we ordered some food, beer tube and soju .We didnt even get to finish our food and drinks one of the waitress asked if we can leave bc there was a reservation ?? We was there less than an hour

After waiting close to an hour to even be as much as checked on, we got up and left. Of course, we still paid even though they 100% didn’t deserve it. $24 dollars for drinking only half of our drinks and eating half of the appetizer. They automatically assumed we wanted to give a 20% tip as if they were completely oblivious to how awful their service was. We should have just left without paying. Absolutely not worth it and will never go back.

The service was horrible. A group of us went and when ordering drinks she asked to see our IDs, when given she took the ID to someone else because she didn't know if we were 21 or not... She came back admitting she didn't know how to do the math. Since some people in our group were underaged, she said we couldn't order drinks. Then she came back to us again and said we could as long as we ordered bottled alcohol? Which we already planned on getting. When she brought us our drinks, she brought 3 beers that we didn't order and not our drinks we did order. The meal took a long time to get to our table, just for it to taste okay, not worth the price. She asked if we were paying together or separate and we told her separate but when she came back she said that the machine didn't allow separate checks. So we ended up charging it on one card that included a 20%tip already which was stupid. Service needs a lot of help and the outfits they wear are very unprofessional.

Like a nightclub, this place is darkly lit, serves copious liquor, blasts Korean pop music, and overcharges for drinks.  Like a restaurant, they have a full food menu and regular tables where people can sit.  Yea.  It's confusing.  I heard great things from this one girl and have always been curious.  While milling around in the area around 10pm on a Thursday, I decided to check it out.  This is not a great place to go alone, even though everyone is drinking and there's a clubby vibe to it, it's not conducive to meeting new people since everyone's sitting at set tables and many people are speaking in Korean.  I sat in the corner and ordered some fried chicken wings.  I love chicken wings.  It was 8 pieces for $14, which is pretty expensive, at over $2 per wing after tax and tip.  Maybe it's just been a while since I've been to Bon Chon in NYC.  The Korean pop video made me feel super weird.  It featured a really pretty guy with tattoos who thinks of himself as really tough and "urban."  I sat next to two guys speaking Korean and didn't want to interrupt them (it's weird table crashing people who might not speak English.  Plus, it's two guys).  So I saw the next table over looked liked interesting people.  A mix of white/Asian, guys/girls.  They all looked bored, on their phones, with tons of food and drinks untouched.  I asked if I could join them and long story short, it was a really fun night.  They got 25 bottles of soju for 5 people.  Insane.  The chicken wings I got were lackluster and definitely not worth $2/piece.  I probably won't really get food here, as it's overpriced and nothing special.  They bank on drunk people making poor decisions.  Which seemed to be the theme at my table as we struggled to finish the 25th bottle of soju and they drunk counted $20 bills to pay off the $500 or $600 that was owed.  Insane.

As a Korean, it's been hard for me to find a truly authentic Korean restaurant/bar in Boston. Sojuba is that and more. It's not only authentic, but it has a super exciting vibe that I haven't found anywhere else in the area. They play the latest K-pop, hip hop, and electronic music, the lighting is fun, and the owners are incredibly friendly. Of course the food is delicious (try the fried chicken!) and the soju is obviously amazing (peach is the best one imho). I came with a group of 20 people for a friend's birthday party, and the staff was incredibly accommodating and helpful. The space was large enough for all of us, and everyone tried their very best to make sure we had everything we needed. After coming here, I don't think I can ever go back to the other places I used to visit!

This place is trash. My friends and I where charged 20% tip without consent and the tips were added after tax, allowing them to get more tips. After asking if we could tip before tax the server was nice enough to void the the tip and let us choose our rate. Now, we were going to tip them 20% because the food was really good (considering this is my first time eating Korean food ) and the severs were polite to us. However, when we were all charge wrong amounts and when we asked why they server admitted he made a mistake. People make mistakes so i can understand, however the owner of the place decided to jump in the conversation for no reason and started yelling at me an my friend. He did not even know what we were taking about and all of a sudden he started cussing at us, told me I don’t know what I am talking about and did not give me the opportunity to explain myself. The owner completely unvalidated our problems and told us ‘we don’t care if you want to tip us %15 or 20%, we don’t care about your $1.50’, then he started yelling at the server too. He was verbally abusive to me and my friends and recorded a video of me without my consent.  I also noticed that he was serving alcohol to minors, or at least he never asked them for their ID. The servers were super sweet and they all deserve a raise because dealing with someone who is so negative is definitely a challenge. At the end the server was nice enough to come find us and apologized for the owner’s behavior. If you’re just coming here to dance or grab food to go then yes I recommend this place. But if you are trying to have a good night with your friends PLEASE GO TO DOMINOS instead, you will probably get a better experience.

No good. Friend bring me here but we find out this people put hidden tip. so we pay tip two times by mistake and we only 3 people. Always check receip even if you get drunk here they will try put hidden tip. Very bad they are scaming customers.

This is probably one of the few restaurants where I am actually taking the time to describe how horrible the service was. Was the food incredible? Sure. But, given how expensive this restaurant was, I was expecting impeccable service, and it was also not busy. My party of five was charged 20% gratuity after tax, which I have NEVER seen before. I have only ever been charged 18% gratuity with parties of 8 or more, and the service was incredible in all instances, but not here. When we requested to add our own tip, since we were given no indication of the added tip before hand (not on the menu to the best of our knowledge), we initially were provided with that. However, the manager or owner decided to scream and verbally harass my friend, demanding to know why we cannot tip 20%. I cannot believe this restaurateur went out of his way to scream at a patron. I will not be going back to this establishment, and I urge everyone reading this to do the same.

Lots of food and drink choices for fairly reasonable prices. Seated immediately though the service was a little slow and it took a while before we could put an order in, even when it was just during the first opening hour and it was not too busy yet. I liked the atmosphere however and was satisfied with what we ordered.
Nice restaurant with high ceilings

Visited this spot on a weekday when the Red Sox were playing. There was no wait and the staff were very friendly. They were going above and beyond their job to make sure everything was good. The Korean pop music and videos on the TV gives this place a cool and unique atmosphere. The food here is amazing, gotta try the half and half spicy wings. The food here is on the spicy side of things, but definitely flavorful. Will definitely come back again.
Good food and nice staff members. Adding diversity to Fenway area.

Very tasty Korean food! Great atmosphere as well.
So fun

The food was mediocre and the service at start seems tentative but sit long enough and they become a hovering staff trying to get you out the door. My friends and I were there with a large group of 12 that constantly was irering food and drinks, there was no line and after three hours of laughter, eating and lots of drinks the staff asked us if we were going to leave soon...uhhhhh. Other than their slim selection of soju there's nothing special about this place.

This is my second time at Sojuba. Not going to lie, my first visit was kinda mediocre. I felt like the food was decent but fairly overpriced. But after having visited another time around, my opinion has changed. This time we came with a large group and just bought bottle after bottle. I think the true magic of this place is to just come with a huge group of friends and get hammered. Tasty selection of soju. Great vibes, would totally come back.

We actually didn't eat here so this review is not about the food. If you're looking for an "authentic experience", this is not the place. Korean restaurant typically have a bunch of side dishes that come with your entrees-- those are my favorite part. This restaurant does not do that, and seem to be a sports bar with Korean flair (I mean, the waiter said the most popular item was chicken wings). When we got there it was crazy loud with some sort of Russian event happening in the main seating area. The service seems kind and diligent though
Good seafood pancake and fast service
The place looks good, nice environment,  good service, but the food is terrible

Awesome place. nice vibe

Great place to chill, listen to music and have super spicy Korean fried Chicken. Would definitely be back more often if parking was so difficult. Their sojus are great and the prices for everything is reasonable. The music is a bit loud in the evening so expect to come here to bounce your heads rather than to talk to friends. The service is usually pretty great but since it can get pretty packed on the weekends don’t be surprised if you have to wait a while before actually hearing back with your orders (order everything you need at once!)

If you love Korean food and booze, definitely the place to go! They let us take our time since our friend was super late, which was very nice. The food was tasty, although a bit salty. Minus a star because the rice was undercooked. Asked the waitress about it, but did nothing.
Amazing

Great food and greater music. K Pop 4eva!

My favorite Korean joint in all of Boston! Whenever I have Soju and bulgogi cravings I come here! Staff is extremely friendly and efficient. Serving sizes of food is substantial and there's a wide variety of drinks to order. If you're in the area and want some good asian comfort food this is the place to be!
Favorite place for korean food and soju!

I heard a Korean restaurant opened near my school so my friends and I went to try it over the weekend. The place is really nice, and quite big for a Korean restaurant. We were fourth in line on the waiting list, and the host took us to the bar area right away to get our night started. The bar area is just as chill, so we told ourselves that we would just eat at the bar if tables didn’t open up in the next 30 min. 25 minutes or so, a table opened up downstairs, and we ordered pretty much everything on the menu. Their original chicken was to die for, and the boodae pot was really really good too. It had a lively vibe with people enjoying themselves everywhere around me. We didn’t mean to go out drinking, but the scene def called for it! Four bottles of soju in, we asked for requests to the DJ and stayed until closing. The servers are super fun and friendly, and the owner came to check on us in the middle of our meal. This is a new gem for me and my friends for sure! I’m glad we don’t need to hike to Allston now to enjoy soju with authentic Korean food!

Boozy Korean restaurant with a nightclub atmosphere!  Food and soju are awesome. Great service too. We came at a busy time on Saturday night so,  naturally,  it took our food a while to get to us. But when we did get it the waitress brought us free shots because we had to wait. Any place that gives me free booze just because we had to wait is definitely wicked awesome (as the local Bostonians might say). I will DEFINITELY be coming back to this place next time I'm in town.
Soju for days
Favorite new place for soju and Korean food !!!!
